Title: Travel Inn
Content: The Travel Inn is another economical lodging property located on the outskirts of Natchez; located just a couple of minutes from downtown.

Title: Katie's Ladies Apparel
Content: Katie's Ladies is a local favorite dress shop with everything from casual to cocktail wear. If you're in Natchez with your girlfriends for a shopping spree, take the 2-3 minute drive out Franklin St. and include Katie's in your shopping itinerary. You'll be glad you did.

Title: Bowie Outfitters
Content: Bowie Outfitters offers an incredible selection of outdoor apparel and sports gear. Specializing in firearms and archery equipment, Bowie Outfitters carries Orvis, Browning, Mossy Oak and Drake apparel. The store also boasts a large selection of hunting boots such as Rocky and LaCrosse, making Bowie Outfitters the place to find the perfect gift for every outdoorsman and a great place for shopping in Mississippi.

Title: Natchez Convention Center
Content:
The Natchez Convention Center is the flagship of a triplet venue complex, offering over 23,000 square feet of divisible function space downstairs, including three meeting rooms, an executive board room, 5,100 square feet of pre-function area, a fully equipped concession area, a full service kitchen, and wi-fi throughout the building. The siblings of the convention center are the Community Center and The Natchez City Auditorium. 
Upstairs offers 6,670 square feet of divisible meeting space, including 8 meeting rooms, three of which have balconies overlooking Main Street, and five overlooking the main exhibit hall of the first floor. Combine all of this with first class audio/visual equipment and a superb professional staff with a passion for successful events, and you have more than the basic needs to create a great event. It's located in the heart of downtown Natchez, within walking distance of lots of retail shops, some of the city's best dining establishments, and a number of attractions that can be visited or toured.

Title: Natchez Civic Center
Content: Immediately across the street from the rear of the Convention Center is the Community Center. Of the entire buildings 6,695 sq. feet, 5,000 sq. feet of the building can be utilized quite nicely for receptions, banquets, and small trade shows, as well as theater and class-room style seating. It functions very well for overflow from the Convention Center should your meeting or trade show require just a bit more space that the NCC has to spare.

Title: Pampered Soul, The
Content: Although the name would obviously describe a shoe store, you'll be pleasantly surprised to find dresses and other ladies apparel at The Pampered Soul. From Casual to Formal wear, the store carries a nice variety of clothing to fit any fashion taste. Stop in while antiquing on Franklin St.

Title: Hello, Gorgeous!
Content: Hello, Gorgeous! is a unique salon located in the heart of downtown. Stylists Suzanne Burrows and Jeffery Whittington offer trademark hair styling which will surely enhance your beauty on your wedding day. They can make the groom look good as well. Stop in for a consultation while you're making plans for your big day, and mark "hair-styling" off your list.

Title: Relax Inn
Content: Located on the South end of Natchez just passed Natchez Regional Hospital...you'll find this economical motel tucked off the highway just enough to buffer highway noise to assure a good nights rest.

Title: Longwood
Content: Longwood is the crown jewel of the historic properties of Natchez and can be toured seven days a week between 9:00 a.m. and 4:30 p.m. with the last tour available at 4:30. Longwood is a "must see" for every visitor as it has a history unlike any other in the area. Tickets are available through Natchez Pilgrimage Tours located in the Natchez Visitor Center.

Title: Lansdowne
Content: Lansdowne is a modest Greek Revival style residence, a beautifully preserved document of mid-nineteenth-century taste in architecture and interior decoration. According to family tradition, Lansdowne was constructed in 1853 for George M. Marshall and his wife Charlotte, whose descendants still occupy the house today. The home is often available for tour during the Spring or Fall Pilgrimage seasons.

Title: Ja'Nel's Flowers & Gifts & Buttercup Bakery
Content:
Ja'Nel's is one of the few florists that has been a Natchez household name for a few decades. You will be pleasantly surprised by the variety in their inventory of flora and be assured that arrangements they create for your wedding day will be a highlight of guest conversation. Call or stop by for a consultation for your big day. 
-UPDATE-
Ja'Nel's Flowers and Gifts is now also home to Buttercup Bakery! In addition to fresh flowers, silks, plants and gifts we will also be offering fresh home-style baked goods. Come by and check out all of the delicious home-style goodies made just like Granny used to make them! We use only the good stuff... real butter and completely from scratch! Our daily selections will vary so don't miss out! We look forward to seeing you!

Title: Rosalie
Content:
Rosalie is located on the Mississippi Bluff near the site of the Natchez Indians' massacre of the French at Fort Rosalie. Completed in 1823, the architectural design of the antebellum home became the prototype for later mansions in Natchez and across the South. The design is cubical in nature with two-story columns supporting both a front portico and a rear full-width gallery. It was the headquarters of the Union Army during the War Between the States. This National Historic Landmark is now owned by the Mississippi State Society DAR.
Tours every hour 9:00 a.m.-4:00 p.m.; Last tour begins at 4:00 p.m. Please call about holiday hours and arrangements for special tours.

Title: Natchez-Adams County Airport
Content: The Natchez-Adams County Airport is a top-notch aviation facility, and although there are no commercial airline services offered, the airport services a large number of private and corporate traffic. The NACA provides jet fuel and some maintenance services to aircraft of a variety of types.

Title: Eccentricities, LLC
Content: Eccentricities, LLC in downtown Natchez specializes in retail and consignment items, including antiques, vintage and contemporary home accents. Located in The Cole House c. 1875, you will also find a wide variety of beautiful jewelry, candles and bath soaps. Stop by Tuesday-Thursday from 10:00 a.m.-5:00 p.m. or call to schedule an appointment or plan a special event!

Title: Andrew's Tavern
Content: Andrew's Tavern is conveniently located in the heart of downtown. One of the popular Natchez bars, they have flat screen TV's for sports.

Title: Magnolia Bluffs Casino
Content: Magnolia Bluffs Casino is designed to look like the old Learned Saw Mill which stood near the new facility until about 1940. The casino has plenty of slot and video poker machines and 10 gaming tables, along with a buffet style restaurant and an Italian Steakhouse which has exceptional views of the Mississippi River. Valet parking is available and there is ample parking in a two-story garage just North of the casino's front door. Magnolia Bluffs is open 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.

Title: Magnolia Cottage
Content: Magnolia Cottage offers a quaint setting for small, intimate wedding ceremonies. Check their special offers and packages for details or call Jackie to get more information about all that Magnolia Cottage will put together to make your wedding day extra special.

Title: Southern Style Restaurant, Catering & Bar
Content: Southern Style Catering offers home-style meals with a variety of meats, starches and vegetables prepared for a sit down dinner or heavy Hors d' Ouerves. When it comes to offering your guests or meeting attendees a taste of great Southern cuisine, you simply can't go wrong with Southern Style Catering.

Title: Holiday Inn Express & Suites
Content:
We invite you to experience the Holiday Inn Express & Suites Natchez.
Located within walking distance of historic downtown Natchez, MS. 
Our limited service Natchez hotel features sweeping landscapes of the Mighty Mississippi River, complimentary breakfast and a relaxing stay. Guests will enjoy our complimentary high speed Internet with both wireless and wired capabilities. The hotel's state of the art 24 hour fitness center allows for guests to maintain their daily routine. All rooms include a microwave, refrigerator and a minimum of 37" HDTVs.
The Southern hospitality you have come to expect from a historic Mississippi town will be exceeded during your stay at the Holiday Inn Express & Suites Natchez.

Title: Natchez National Cemetery
Content: Natchez National Cemetery dates to 1866, one of 21 national historic cemeteries established in that year. Located on a bluff overlooking the Mississippi River, the site's topography influenced its unique layout of irregular shaped burial sections, terraced hillsides, and gravel and grass pathways.

simpleview_listing_LISTINGKEYWORDS: Natchez Coffee, Steampunk Coffee Roasters, Live music, Natchez Music, Natchez nightlife, Nightlife
Title: Steampunk Coffee Roasters/Papi Y Papi
Content: Open Tuesday-Sunday 8-5, this isn't your typical Coffee Shop. With such a quirky, cool atmosphere you'll want to hang out all day and night! Steampunk is located one block from the bluff in a newly restored brick cabin dating back to 1868. They are a specialty coffee roaster and they carry an extensive list of coffee equipment and other related items. They even have an espresso bar, which serves espresso, cappuccino,lattes, pour over, french press, siphon vacuum coffee and Turkish.

Title: A Gallerie
Content: A quaint little shop in the heart of downtown Natchez, filled with local designs, unique gifts and happiness for the home.

Title: Rolling River Reloaded
Content:
Located in the heart of downtown among quaint gift shops, short walking distance from all downtown hotels and Bed & Breakfasts. Rolling River Bistro is open Tuesday - Saturday for Lunch and Dinner.The Bistro serves until 11:00 pm on the weekends. LIVE music every Thursday, Friday and Saturday nights. Serving a fresh, seasonal menu that may include fried crawfish tails, Lobster Ravioli, seafood lasagna, grilled fish, steaks, sandwiches and the city's most amazing salads. The Signature Cocktails are stellar and refreshing. 

A bright unique dining area and a separate listening room is available for entertainment, private dining receptions, parties and meetings for up to 100 seated and 200 reception style. The listening room has a large 12 foot projection screen with HD projector. Motor coaches are welcome and lectures can be arranged for private lunches. 

Rolling River Bistro is also a full service caterer for events & meeting off-site as well. A catering menu and casserole menu is available for local gatherings and can be delivered. The staff has extensive experience in meeting & event planning.. Make the Bistro one of your stops on your visit to Natchez - We would love to meet you!

Title: Isabella House of Natchez
Content: Isabella House is a circa 1885 cottage with vintage character and charm located in the Downriver Historic District of Natchez, Mississippi. It has been lovingly renovated from a state of total disrepair and is available for nightly and weekly stays comfortably accommodating 2-4 guests. Although furnished with many unique and antique pieces, it still offers modern conveniences such as cable, internet, a dishwasher and washer/dryer as well as complimentary snacks and beverages. The rear courtyard is spacious and private and has a grill and chiminea for guest use. At Isabella House, you'll be within walking distance of wonderful downtown shops, restaurants and entertainment, but, since the 1920s Monitor Top refrigerator keeps the coldest drinks in town, you might not want to leave the back porch!

Title: Camp Restaurant, The
Content: With the recent changes to beer laws in the state of Mississippi, new wonderful beers are now available to the public. New breweries are opening all across the state and region and each is offering their own special touches and brewing styles to beer. The Camp is excited to share these beers with locals and visitors to the Natchez area. Here you can sip a beer and enjoy good food on our porch overlooking the Mighty Mississippi River, or sit inside and watch sports on one of our many large flat-screen TVs. We even have a courtyard in the back for a little more peace. Whatever you choose, we know you'll have a good time!

Title: Castle Restaurant & Pub, The
Content: Located in an original 1790's carriage house and stables, The Castle is the perfect setting for a wonderful dining experience. Having received the Wine Spectator, "Award of Excellence" since its opening in December of 2000, The Castle Restaurant has a wine selection compared to no other establishment in our area. The Castle Pub is a cozy English-style pub with an extensive bar and signature drink menu. Here, guests can order from The Castle Restaurant or select appetizers from the Pub menu. The Pub boasts a large selection of domestic and foreign beers.

Title: Arabella Massage Therapy
Content: Dan and Julia Kelly offer professional massage services to the entire bridal party who are looking for a way to relax before the big Natchez wedding day. Massage styles offered at Arabella include Swedish Massage, Deep Tissue/Trigger Point Therapy, Hot Stone Massage, Myofascial (Muscle/fascia) Release Polarity

Title: Magnolia Hall
Content:
Magnolia Hall's location in the heart of Natchez's downtown historic district places you
and your guests within short blocks of hotels, shops, and dining choices. The historic
home itself presents many options on how the ceremony and the related festivities are
planned. The entire home and its grounds are yours rendering all events there elegant,
southern, and memorable.

Title: Natchez Civic Center
Content: Immediately across the street from the rear of the Convention Center is the Community Center. Of the entire buildings 6,695 sq. feet, 5,000 sq. feet of the building can be utilized quite nicely for receptions, banquets, as well as ceremony space. The location itself cannot be beat!

Title: C'est Jolie, A Boutique Salon
Content: C'est Jolie is a boutique salon offering the pampering every girl needs! In this truly unique atmosphere, you'll feel like the true princess you are! Give them a call today to set up your appointment!

Title: Frogmore Cotton Plantation & Gins
Content:
Selected by Rand McNally as a "MUST SEE" site in South, this 1,800 acre early 19th century cotton plantation has been perfectly preserved. There are several different tour options for individuals or groups. Listen to the slave customs, secret music, and their surprising relationships with the master, mistress, and overseer all while walking through authentically furnished slave quarters, a rare steam gin, and other plantation dependencies. Tours also include the computerized farming and ginning of today. And don't forget to end your trip to Frogmore with a stop in the plantation store museum and gift shop. 

A short 20 minute drive west from Natchez, Frogmore Plantation is open year round. However, tours are by reservation only from November 16 - March 7. Please call 318-757-2453 or 318-757-3333 for more information.

Title: Downtown Karla Brown
Content:
Downtown Karla Brown offers over five different tours. Choose from our 3 or 6-hour Natchez History Tours where we visit Antebellum homes, a local winery, a trading post, as well as one of our fabulous local eateries. You may decide, instead, to choose our fascinating Vicksburg Civil War Tour which includes a stop at the Emerald Mound, the Windsor Ruins and a 3-hour long narrated tour of the Vicksburg National Military Park. You will work up an appetite as we make the scene at your choice of delightful and delicious local cuisine. 

For those who are more actively adventurous, we offer an epic bicycle tour that covers 3 days, 2 nights and an impressive 100 miles of scenic peddling on the striking historic Natchez Trace Parkway. 

We also offer a 2-hour ghostly getaway that takes us on a drive around Natchez to learn about local haunts and legends, as well as a journey into a dark, old occupied building! 

For the more literary types among you, we offer a 2.5-hour book tour covering over 40 stops that has us visiting many of the places Greg Iles mentions in his first three novels of the Penn Cage series, The Quiet Game, Turning Angel and The Devil's Punchbowl. 

Downtown Karla Brown also offers a tour following the locations mentioned in Greg Illes' newest trilogy of Natchez Burning, The Bone Tree and Mississippi Blood.

You can also enjoy a pleasant drive around Natchez while being guided through a brimming catalog of 45 destinations including antebellum homes and other historic destinations.

Title: Little Tokyo Japanese Steakhouse
Content: We are Natchez's only hibachi grill. Whether you are dining at one of our beautiful tables or at our sushi bar, you will be very pleased at our selection and preparation of fine appetizers, sushi, sashimi, rolls, special rolls, chef's specials and special entrees. We look forward to seeing you soon!

Title: My Shoe Kloset
Content: My Shoe Kloset, located in the heart of downtown Natchez, provides quality and affordable shoes, jewelry and accessories. With one of the largest collections of accessories in town, this is a must stop for any fashionista! Open 10-7pm Monday-Saturday, allow them to fulfill your accessory needs!

Listing Amenity: Breakfast Included|Credit Cards Accepted|Historic Property|Internet Access|Laundry Facility Available|Outdoor Pool|Pets Allowed (under 25lbs)|Private Bath|River Views
Title: Weymouth Hall
Content: A majestic property overlooking the river, Weymouth Hall has a few well appointed guest rooms and guests can enjoy an evening cocktail while watching the sunset from this fantastic vantage point. Just a minute from downtown.

Title: Miss-Lou Tours
Content: Miss-Lou Tours boasts a fabulous menu of tours, experiences and adventures in the heart of the Mississippi/Louisiana Region, and is dedicated to providing high-quality diverse, fun and challenging experiences and adventures. We can customize your adventure to give you the best and most rewarding experience. Our tours include knowledgeable local guides and can be combined into a multi-day visit incorporating everything from fishing, hunting, photography, kayaking, African-American History, American Indian History, Churches and so much more! Give us a call today and let us set you up with your next adventure!

Title: Duncan Park
Content:
Located in the heart of Natchez, Duncan Park offers bike and running trails along with a lovely 18-hole golf course, tennis courts and several baseball fields. If you are interested in an afternoon bike ride, head over to Duncan Park for a nice ride along one of their pretty nature trails.
Duncan Park Golf Course is a Public Facility where tourist are always welcome.
"Come out an play a Piece of History"

Title: Roux 61
Content:
Roux 61 cares about every guest and every plate, and has an atmosphere that is 2nd to none. That's why their motto is "great team, great food, great service". 
On their menu you will find everything from seafood & steak to pasta and even alligator cheesecake! With delicious food, generous portions, and a top of the line staff, you'll want to come back again and again. 
They also have an extensive drink menu, oyster bar and live music several days of the week.

Roux 61, the ONLY way to great food.

Title: Choctaw Hall
Content:
Choctaw Hall was built around 1836 and features a blend of Greek Revival to Federal styles. 

Our Bed and Breakfast floor boasts four separate Queen bed suites connected by a comfortable living room and 24/7 access to self-serve snacks, light treats, an assortment of teas, and of course coffee. Our guests receive vouchers for a full breakfast of choice at nearby restaurants.

simpleview_listing_LISTINGKEYWORDS: Concord Quarters, Bed & Breakfast, Bed and Breakfast, B & B
Title: Concord Quarters
Content: Original slave quarters from the 1820's, Concord Quarters sits atop a knoll overlooking natural park-like landscaped acres. Nestled in a community rich in culture, walk out the door and enjoy a song and sermon at one of the oldest, primitive Baptist churches in the city. Across the street, you can enjoy wine tasting and tours of the Old South Winery, famous for their Muscadine wine. Breakfast is served every morning of your stay. We offer three, well-appointed bedrooms to choose from, and beautiful location for weddings. Concord Quarters is located just North of the city, about 5 minutes from downtown. Take in the splendor of massive oak trees and magnolias and experience the soul of southern hospitality.

Title: City Sightseeing Natchez
Content:
Double-Decker Open-Top City Tour Visit Natchez’s Top Attractions

Over 40 spectacular Hop On Hop Off sights and attractions. Hop On our double-decker open-top TOUR bus at any stop and enjoy the ride through historic Natchez. Hop Off and spend as much time as you like at any of our stops. Tours: Tue - Sun 10:00am-2:00pm.
Tickets available for purchase at the Natchez Visitor Center, Natchez Convention Center, Monmouth Historic Inn or Natchez Grand Hotel.

Listing Amenity: Breakfast Included|Historic Property|Internet Access|Outdoor Pool|Private Bath
Title: Burn, The
Content:
Built in 1834 to be the residence of John P. Walworth, a wealthy planter, merchant, banker, and politician, the Burn is the oldest documented Greek Revival residence in Natchez, Mississippi. Listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1979, the Burn was built on a knoll to the north of the old town area of Natchez.

The house is one-and-a-half-story Greek Revival double-pile central hall plan building built of frame construction upon a brick basement. It has a five bay east-facing façade with a pedimented portico supported by four fluted Doric columns.
